<p><font face="Arial Black"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>Abstract
Interface Design</font></font></font></center>

<p><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>• The
following will be specified</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Which interface objects to perceive</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– The way different navigational objects will look like</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Which interface objects will activate navigation</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– The way multimedia interface objects will be synchronized</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Which interface transformations will take place</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>•
Use ADV(Abstract Data View) design approach for describing the user interface</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2></font></font></font>&nbsp;
